name: Dark Alakazam
flavorText: Almost as if it were being controlled by something else, it never changes expressions, even in the middle of battle.
Attack1Text: You may switch Dark Alakazam with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

name: Dark Arbok
flavorText: Freezes its prey with its stare. If you should encounter one, remember not to look into its eyes.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.) If that Pokémon has a Pokémon Power, that power stops working until the end of your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Dark Blastoise
flavorText: An aggressive Pokémon that tackles anything it sees.
Attack1Text: Does 30 damage plus 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Dark Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack. You can't add more than 40 damage in this way.
Attack2Text: Dark Blastoise does 10 damage to itself. Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Dark Blastoise during your opponent's next turn. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

name: Dark Charizard
flavorText: Seemingly possessed, it spews fire like a volcano, trying to burn all it sees.
Attack2Text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Fire Energy cards attached to Dark Charizard. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads. Discard a number of Fire Energy cards attached to Dark Charizard equal to the number of heads.

name: Dark Dragonite
flavorText: Sometimes called "The God of Destruction." Its wings are able to support it in spite of its massive weight.
Ability1Text: When you play Dark Dragonite from your hand, search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Dark Dugtrio
flavorText: Digs large sinkholes in the ground and tries to trap its enemies in them.
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent's Active Pokémon retreats, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this power does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.) This power stops working while Dark Dugtrio is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage; if heads, this attack does 20 damage.

name: Dark Golbat
flavorText: Sneaks up silently on its prey and attacks it from behind, sometimes killing it with one bite.
Ability1Text: When you play Dark Golbat from your hand, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. If you do, Dark Golbat does 10 damage to that Pokémon. Apply Weakness and Resistance.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

name: Dark Gyarados
flavorText: Normally found only in the deep ocean, it has recently been seen in shallow waters as well.
Ability1Text: When Dark Gyarados is Knocked Out by an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this power does 20 damage for each Water Energy attached to Dark Gyarados to the Pokémon that Knocked Out Dark Gyarados. Apply Weakness and Resistance. This power doesn't work if Dark Gyarados is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Dark Hypno
flavorText: Carries a pendulum with it always. Sometimes appears near less-traveled roads and schools at dusk.
Attack2Text: Your opponent flips a number of coins equal to the number of Pokémon on his or her Bench. This attack does 20 damage times the number of tails. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

name: Dark Machamp
flavorText: It is almost impossible to defend against a Machamp's four powerful arms.
Attack2Text: Your opponent shuffles his or her Active Pokémon and all cards attached to it into his or her deck. This attack can't be used if your opponent has no Benched Pokémon.

name: Dark Magneton
flavorText: The number of incidents of hackers using Magnetons to damage computer systems is steadily increasing.
Attack1Text: Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokémon has any basic Energy cards attached to it, choose 1 of them. If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose 1 of them and attach that Energy card to it.

name: Dark Slowbro
flavorText: It loves nothing better than to be left alone, and so sometimes ends up being manipulated by unscrupulous people.
Ability1Text: When you play Dark Slowbro from your hand, choose up to 3 Basic Pokémon and/or Evolution cards from your discard pile and put them into your hand.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Dark Vileplume
flavorText: Perhaps because of their strong-smelling pollen, other Pokémon do not approach areas where Vileplumes live.
Ability1Text: No Trainer cards can be played. This power stops working while Dark Vileplume is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads. If you get 2 or more heads, Dark Vileplume is now Confused (after doing damage).

name: Dark Weezing
flavorText: Researchers have observed these Pokémon reproducing in industrial waste sites.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage times the total number of Koffings, Weezings, and Dark Weezings in play (Apply Weakness and Resistance.). Then, this attack does 20 damage to each Koffing, Weezing, and Dark Weezing (even your own). Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned; if tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

Attack1Text: You may switch Dark Alakazam with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

Ability1Text: When you play Dark Slowbro from your hand, choose up to 3 Basic Pokémon and/or Evolution cards from your discard pile and put them into your hand.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

Ability1Text: No Trainer cards can be played. This power stops working while Dark Vileplume is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads. If you get 2 or more heads, Dark Vileplume is now Confused (after doing damage).

name: Dark Weezing
flavorText: Researchers have observed these Pokémon reproducing in industrial waste sites.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage times the total number of Koffings, Weezings, and Dark Weezings in play (Apply Weakness and Resistance.). Then, this attack does 20 damage to each Koffing, Weezing, and Dark Weezing (even your own). Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned; if tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Dark Charmeleon
flavorText: Its tail is incredibly strong, able to lift up to 5 adult men.
Attack2Text: Use this attack only if there are any Fire Energy cards attached to Dark Charmeleon. Flip a coin. If heads, discard 1 of those Energy cards. If tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).

name: Dark Dragonair
flavorText: As is fitting for a legendary Pokémon, it has many strange powers, including the ability to make rain or snow fall.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for an Evolution card. Show it to your opponent and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Dark Dragonair is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 20 damage.

name: Dark Electrode
flavorText: Some researchers hypothesize that Electrode may actually be a form of energy instead of having an actual body.
Attack2Text: Take all Energy cards attached to Dark Electrode and attach them to your Benched Pokémon (in any way you choose). If you have no Benched Pokémon, discard all Energy cards attached to Dark Electrode.

name: Dark Flareon
flavorText: A Pokémon with a hot temper that can't be controlled once it's angered. Capable of breathing flames hotter than 3000°.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Dark Flareon.
Attack2Text: Use this attack only if there are any Fire Energy cards attached to Dark Flareon. Flip a coin. If heads, discard 1 of those Energy cards and this attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 30 damage.

name: Dark Gloom
flavorText: Its pollen has such a strong smell that it even confuses itself at times.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused; if tails, your Active Pokémon is now Confused. This power can't be used if Dark Gloom is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Dark Golduck
flavorText: When Psyducks evolve, their headaches disappear and they find themselves in possession of formidable mental powers.
Attack1Text: Discard 1 Energy card attached to Dark Golduck in order to draw up to 3 cards.

name: Dark Jolteon
flavorText: A dangerous Pokémon when angered. It likes to playfully shock people with the electricity it stores within its body.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, Dark Jolteon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Dark Kadabra
flavorText: Some people say that Kadabras are responsible for many of the mysterious events reported in the news.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a card from your hand in order to draw a card. This power can't be used if Dark Kadabra is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

name: Dark Machoke
flavorText: While normally peaceful and friendly, the number of incidents involving cruel Machokes is rising.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and switch it with the Defending Pokémon. Do the damage to the new Defending Pokémon. This attack can't be used if your opponent has no Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokémon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)

name: Dark Muk
flavorText: Muks appear suddenly, spreading sludge everywhere. Whenever one appears in a city, panic ensues.
Ability1Text: As long as Dark Muk is your Active Pokémon, your opponent pays ColorlessColorless more to retreat his or her Active Pokémon. This power stops working while Dark Muk is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Dark Persian
flavorText: Popular with women because of its beautiful fur. The leader of the Rockets keeps one as a pet.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and switch it with the Defending Pokémon. This attack can't be used if your opponent has no Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Dark Primeape
flavorText: Although Primeapes have always been mean, lately they seem to be becoming even more vicious and frenzied.
Ability1Text: If Dark Primeape does any damage while it's Confused (even to itself), it does 30 more damage.
Attack1Text: Dark Primeape is now Confused (after doing damage).

name: Dark Rapidash
flavorText: A wild, uncontrollable Pokémon. When running, it looks like a comet streaking through the sky.
Attack2Text: You may discard 1 Fire Energy card attached to Dark Rapidash when you use this attack. If you do and if your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose 1 of them and this attack does 10 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Dark Vaporeon
flavorText: A Pokémon capable of controlling water, so it is capable of creating giant whirlpools.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokémon has any Energy cards attached to it, choose 1 of them and discard it.

name: Dark Wartortle
flavorText: A Pokémon with a negative attitude, it hides in its shell whenever it's in a bad mood—which is often.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: If an attack does damage to Dark Wartortle during your opponent's next turn (even if Dark Wartortle is Knocked Out), Dark Wartortle attacks the Defending Pokémon for an equal amount of damage.

name: Magikarp
flavorText: Recent research has revealed the presence of dragon DNA in this species of Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for an Evolution card named Gyarados or Dark Gyarados and put it on Magikarp. (This counts as evolving Magikarp.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Porygon
flavorText: More and more people play the slots every day, trying to win a Porygon.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon has a Weakness, you may change it to a type of your choice other than Colorless.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Abra
flavorText: It teleports itself away from danger, making it difficult to capture.
Attack1Text: Shuffle Abra into your deck. (Discard all cards attached to Abra.)
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Charmander
flavorText: Many people find it cute and try to hold it, only to be burned by its tail.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may take 1 Fire Energy card attached to 1 of your other Pokémon and attach it to Charmander. This power can't be used if Charmander is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Dark Raticate
flavorText: A Raticate's front teeth are incredibly powerful; it can destroy a two-story house with them in 5 minutes.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Diglett
flavorText: It follows Onixes in their tunnels, looking for scraps of food they have left behind.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

name: Dratini
flavorText: The capture of the first Dratini inspired the search for other legendary Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Drowzee
flavorText: Not popular with girls because of its attitude. Can often be heard muttering to itself in a low voice.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep; if tails, your Active Pokémon is now Asleep. This power can't be used if Drowzee is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: A rare and unique Pokémon about which little is known, as few have been captured.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

name: Ekans
flavorText: A carnivore that swallows its prey whole. Pidgeys and Spearows are its favorite food.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Grimer
flavorText: It has recently been found that Grimers are formed in waste-processing plants, and can move into towns via sewers.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

name: Koffing
flavorText: First discovered in a weapons factory, this Pokémon can now be found almost anywhere.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Machop
flavorText: It's said that not even pro wrestlers can take down a Machop.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: It is said that enough Magnemites and Magnetons gather in one place, they can create a powerful magnetic barrier.
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Magnemite, Magneton, and Dark Magneton on your Bench.

name: Mankey
flavorText: Normally friendly, it quickly becomes angry if it doesn't get what it wants.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 20 damage.

name: Meowth
flavorText: A popular Pokémon that earns money for its owner with its "Pay Day" ability.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon and flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

name: Oddish
flavorText: It wanders around at night sowing its seeds to create more Oddishes.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Ponyta
flavorText: A gentle grass-eater, it will allow riders on its back. However, anyone attempting to do so must be careful not to get burned.
Attack1Text: Discard 1 Fire Energy card attached to Ponyta in order to use this attack.

name: Psyduck
flavorText: It is often seen holding its head in its paws, as if it were suffering from a headache.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Psyduck but not used to pay for this attack. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

name: Rattata
flavorText: Loves to eat walnuts, chestnuts, cheese, and milk.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may switch 1 of your Prizes with the top card of your deck. This power can't be used if Rattata is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

name: Slowpoke
flavorText: Although it knows how to fish, no other intelligent behavior has been detected in it.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to Slowpoke. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: Cute Pokémon that charms people with its innocent eyes. Loves swimming all day long.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: Usually seen only in power plants, it is sometimes seen in towns, apparently using the power lines to travel.

name: Zubat
flavorText: Lives in dark caves. Can occasionally be seen at night, when it flies in search of food.

name: Dark Raichu
flavorText: Stores up electricity in its body, then suddenly releases it to surprise and shock everyone.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, flip another coin. If the second coin is heads, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. If the second coin is tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
